This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with search ranking and recommendation systems. It also involves machine learning models such as Learning-to-Rank (LTR) models, which are commonly used in IR. 

The paper also involves handling biases in data, which is a common problem in machine learning. This makes the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) a likely candidate as well. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as text analysis, which falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). 

The paper also involves online testing and experimentation, which falls under the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY). 

Finally, the paper involves data analysis and modeling, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
